@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Ti_Coune" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, the game requires a 68020(+)
Amiga with Workbench 2.0 or higher.

                             How to play?

  The game is played on an 8 by 8 spaces area in which are walls
that have been randomly placed here and there. Ti_Coune is
represented by a smiling face icon, located at the upper left
position. The exit is located at the lower right position and is
surrounded by a coloured 'fence' (represented by a small square).
An icon representing a small key, of the same colour used by the
fence around the exit, is placed somewhere on the game board.

  To move Ti_Coune, there must be 3 walls (any one of the borders
of the game board can be considered as a wall) and one opening
around him.

  To change walls, click on one position, whether or not Ti_Coune
is at that position. As the location of the clicked position
(except for any position at the right or lowermost part of the game
board), this will make walls appear or disappear at right, as well
as below that position. The sequence in which walls will appear or
disappear is determined along the following order: Space without
walls, space with a wall at right but no wall below, space with no
wall at right but a wall below, space with both walls at right and
below... and the cycle restarts with a space with no walls.

  If you click on a position at the right of the game board, a wall
will appear or disappear below that position. While clicking at a
lowermost position on the board will make a wall appear or
disappear at the right of that position.

  Before Ti_Coune can get to the exit, he must find a key, which
will remove the fence that surrounds the exit space. Then he will
be able to get to the exit, which will complete the game. The least
amount of moves it takes to get to the exit, the better it is...

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

